FBIS4-39959 "drsov113_b_94006" FBIS-SOV-94-113 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues `Russia's Democratic Choice Party' Holds Founding Congress `Russia's Democratic Choice Party' Holds Founding Congress Political Council Elected LD1306081894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0757 GMT 13 Jun 94 LD1306081894 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Aleksandrova] [Text] Moscow June 13 TASS -- Yegor Gaydar has been elected the chairman of Russia's Democratic Choice Party. The results of voting by secret ballot were announced on Monday, the second day of the party's founding congress proceedings. Gaydar's candidacy was carried by 490 votes to 14. The party's political council was elected as well. On the council are, in particular, Anatoliy Chubays, Fedor Shelov-Kovedyayev, Bella Denisenko, Boris Zolotukhin, Aleksandrr Pochinok, Sergey Yushenkov, Ilya Zaslavskiy and other prominent political and public figures.
